00:39:33,235 --> 00:39:37,734
That's why I've hand-picked some links
below to help you out, you wall flower.

537
00:39:37,823 --> 00:39:38,484
For real?

538
00:39:46,156 --> 00:39:47,929
She's making fun of me.

539
00:40:17,209 --> 00:40:18,556
You know something, Taki?

540
00:40:19,546 --> 00:40:22,874
Today you're... you're like a different person.

541
00:40:32,310 --> 00:40:33,672
Um, Miss Okudera,

542
00:40:34,352 --> 00:40:37,336
You getting hungry? We could get dinner.

543
00:40:39,067 --> 00:40:40,712
Uh. Let's call it a day.

544
00:40:42,483 --> 00:40:43,394
All right.

545
00:40:43,900 --> 00:40:45,207
I could be wrong,

546
00:40:45,793 --> 00:40:47,309
and I'm sorry if I am.

547
00:40:47,409 --> 00:40:47,973
About?

548
00:40:48,434 --> 00:40:52,048
But you used to have a little crush on me, am I right?

549
00:40:53,710 --> 00:40:56,680
But right now, there's someone else you like, huh?

550
00:40:57,068 --> 00:41:00,363
No. No, it's not that.

551
00:41:00,432 --> 00:41:01,302
Really?

552
00:41:01,569 --> 00:41:04,011
There's no one. It's not like that.

553
00:41:04,151 --> 00:41:05,940
Are you sure about that?

554
00:41:07,292 --> 00:41:10,527
Well, thanks for today! See you at work.

555
00:41:25,590 --> 00:41:27,350
By the time the date's over...

556
00:41:27,589 --> 00:41:30,334
...you should be able to see the comet in the sky.

557
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:36,237
What does she mean? Weirdo.

558
00:42:05,030 --> 00:42:07,101
Oh, it's you, Teshi.

559
00:42:08,190 --> 00:42:08,778
No,

560
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:12,177
I just didn't feel like going, that's all. I'm fine.

561
00:42:13,279 --> 00:42:15,527
What? The festival?

562
00:42:18,296 --> 00:42:19,825
Oh, yeah, the comet.

563
00:42:20,061 --> 00:42:22,214
It'll be at its brightest today, right?

564
00:42:23,431 --> 00:42:26,282
Okay, got it. See ya later.

565
00:42:29,794 --> 00:42:33,432
You're just looking forward to seeing
Mitsuha in a yukata, aren'tcha?

566
00:42:33,506 --> 00:42:34,706
I-I am not!

567
00:42:35,090 --> 00:42:37,274
I mean, it didn't even cross my mind.

568
00:42:38,220 --> 00:42:41,478
Y'know, she sounded kinda down when I talked to her.

569
00:42:41,510 --> 00:42:43,569
Maybe she just didn't want a call from ya.

570
00:42:43,689 --> 00:42:44,938
It's not funny!

571
00:42:44,971 --> 00:42:45,691
Sorry to keep ya.

572
00:42:45,716 --> 00:42:46,459
Oh, she's here!

573
00:42:46,484 --> 00:42:47,199
You're late.

574
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:52,534
Mitsuha, what happened to...?

575
00:42:54,044 --> 00:42:55,167
Your hair!

576
00:42:55,942 --> 00:42:58,532
I guess... it's weird.

577
00:43:07,724 --> 00:43:09,537
You think it's gotta do with some guy?

578
00:43:09,562 --> 00:43:11,004
Like... he broke her heart?

579
00:43:11,079 --> 00:43:13,960
Guys always just assume that it has to do with a boy.

580
00:43:14,374 --> 00:43:16,497
She said she felt like cutting it.

581
00:43:16,529 --> 00:43:20,315
Ya sure about that? You really think she
felt like cutting off that much of it?

582
00:43:21,340 --> 00:43:23,073
Hey, guys! I can see it!

583
00:43:41,639 --> 00:43:43,325
Whoa.

584
00:44:02,110 --> 00:44:05,770
The number you are trying to reach is
currently outside the cellular network

585
00:44:05,810 --> 00:44:07,249
or has been turned off due...

586
00:44:10,266 --> 00:44:13,846
I'll just have to tell her how lousy the
date ended up the next time we switch.

587
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:16,153
That's what I thought.

588
00:44:17,443 --> 00:44:17,972
But...

589
00:44:18,625 --> 00:44:23,240
For some reason, the switches Mitsuha
and I'd been going through until now...

590
00:44:24,486 --> 00:44:25,835
they never happened again.

591
00:46:19,183 --> 00:46:19,638
Wha...?

592
00:46:20,526 --> 00:46:23,206
What're...? What're you doing here?

593
00:46:26,639 --> 00:46:28,980
Tsukasa told me, so here I am.

594
00:46:32,810 --> 00:46:34,263
I asked for two things.

595
00:46:34,723 --> 00:46:37,910
To cover my shift,
and to back up my alibi if my dad asked.

596
00:46:37,944 --> 00:46:39,765
Relax, Takagi's gonna take your shift.

597
00:46:39,912 --> 00:46:42,729
Gotcha covered! But you owe me dinner!

598
00:46:43,129 --> 00:46:44,777
So you're all in on it.

599
00:46:44,910 --> 00:46:46,643
You've got everyone worried about you.

600
00:46:46,660 --> 00:46:47,192
Huh?

601
00:46:47,479 --> 00:46:50,618
We can't ignore this. What if somebody's
trying to pull one over on you?

602
00:46:50,645 --> 00:46:51,631
Like catfish?

603
00:46:51,995 --> 00:46:54,176
I mean you met this person online, didn't you?

604
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:56,546
No, not exactly! It's kinda complicated.

605
00:46:56,570 --> 00:46:57,676
Could be from a dating site.

606
00:46:57,701 --> 00:46:58,703
She's not!

607
00:46:59,610 --> 00:47:01,824
It's because you've been acting awfully fishy lately.

608
00:47:01,984 --> 00:47:03,513
So we're keeping an eye on you.

609
00:47:03,530 --> 00:47:05,282
I don't need a baby sitter, okay?

610
00:47:07,698 --> 00:47:08,966
The switches stopped.

611
00:47:09,713 --> 00:47:12,783
My calls never connected and texts never went through.

612
00:47:12,936 --> 00:47:15,674
That's why I decided to go see Mitsuha in person.

613
00:47:17,430 --> 00:47:18,877
I wanted to see her.

614
00:47:19,563 --> 00:47:20,009
But...

615
00:47:22,240 --> 00:47:23,082
What?

616
00:47:23,330 --> 00:47:25,195
You don't know where she is exactly?

617
00:47:25,388 --> 00:47:27,594
The town's landscape is your only clue?

618
00:47:27,853 --> 00:47:28,655
Yeah.

619
00:47:31,393 --> 00:47:33,165
And you can't contact her?

620
00:47:33,583 --> 00:47:35,048
What's that about?

621
00:47:35,501 --> 00:47:37,504
Where are we? You're a terrible tour guide.

622
00:47:37,529 --> 00:47:38,949
'Cause I'm not one!

623
00:47:39,309 --> 00:47:42,237
Oh, well. Guess we'll help you search.

624
00:47:42,580 --> 00:47:45,174
Ah! It's so cute! Look, Taki!

625
00:47:45,679 --> 00:47:46,775
Seriously, guys?

626
00:47:46,872 --> 00:47:48,650
It moved! Aw!

627
00:48:18,216 --> 00:48:19,391
This is a lost cause.

628
00:48:19,416 --> 00:48:23,231
What? After everything that we've done for you today?

629
00:48:25,859 --> 00:48:27,888
You haven't done anything.

630
00:48:31,728 --> 00:48:33,064
One Takayama ramen.

631
00:48:33,214 --> 00:48:34,434
One Takayama ramen.

632
00:48:34,816 --> 00:48:36,234
I guess I'll have the same.

633
00:48:36,420 --> 00:48:37,172
Sure.

634
00:48:37,730 --> 00:48:39,047
Three orders of ramen.

635
00:48:39,197 --> 00:48:39,727
Got it.

636
00:48:42,023 --> 00:48:44,138
Think we can make it back to Tokyo tonight?

637
00:48:44,163 --> 00:48:46,421
Well, I think we'll be cutting it close.

638
00:48:46,446 --> 00:48:47,246
Let me take a look.

639
00:48:47,363 --> 00:48:48,255
'K, thanks.

640
00:48:48,280 --> 00:48:50,492
Wait, Taki, you sure about that?

641
00:48:52,900 --> 00:48:57,330
Yeah. I kinda feel like maybe I've been
barking up the wrong tree this whole time.

642
00:49:01,870 --> 00:49:04,604
Hey. That's a sketch of Itomori, isn't it?

643
00:49:06,760 --> 00:49:07,899
It's drawn really well.

644
00:49:08,560 --> 00:49:10,180
Come take a look at this, Hun!

645
00:49:11,721 --> 00:49:13,263
Yeah, that's Itomori.

646
00:49:13,814 --> 00:49:14,955
It takes me back.

647
00:49:14,996 --> 00:49:17,306
My husband was born and raised there, you know.

648
00:49:17,673 --> 00:49:18,730
Itomori?

649
00:49:21,011 --> 00:49:23,414
Yes, of course! That's the place!

650
00:49:23,655 --> 00:49:25,069
It's nearby, right?

651
00:49:25,776 --> 00:49:26,732
You don't...

652
00:49:27,150 --> 00:49:28,556
Itomori was...

653
00:49:29,005 --> 00:49:30,333
Itomori?

654
00:49:31,029 --> 00:49:31,455
Wait!

655
00:49:31,480 --> 00:49:31,881
But that's where...

656
00:49:31,906 --> 00:49:33,648
Isn't that the area where that comet...?

657
00:50:23,950 --> 00:50:27,041
Hey, is this place really where she's from?

658
00:50:27,261 --> 00:50:30,700
No way. Taki must've just
confused this with somewhere else.

659
00:50:31,119 --> 00:50:32,069
No, I didn't.

660
00:50:33,179 --> 00:50:34,403
This was the place.

661
00:50:35,183 --> 00:50:37,560
This schoolyard. These mountains.

662
00:50:37,690 --> 00:50:40,442
Even this high school here! I remember it all!

663
00:50:40,679 --> 00:50:42,212
There's no way you could.

664
00:50:42,650 --> 00:50:45,769
You've gotta know about that
disaster three years ago, right?

665
00:50:46,633 --> 00:50:48,393
Hundreds of people died.

666
00:50:48,479 --> 00:50:49,135
They died?

667
00:50:50,910 --> 00:50:52,030
Three years ago?

668
00:50:53,006 --> 00:50:54,000
It can't be.

669
00:50:56,116 --> 00:50:57,123
There's no way.

670
00:50:57,720 --> 00:50:58,798
I mean,

671
00:50:59,380 --> 00:51:01,315
I still have the memos she wrote.

672
00:51:19,026 --> 00:51:20,127
They're fading...

673
00:51:30,821 --> 00:51:34,952
Comet Tia-mat, with an orbital period of 1,200 years,

674
00:51:35,393 --> 00:51:38,449
made a close approach to Earth
three years ago in October.

675
00:51:39,677 --> 00:51:42,881
Nobody foresaw that its nucleus
would split at its perigee.

676
00:51:49,765 --> 00:51:53,254
The fragment that broke off of it
became a meteor and struck Japan.

677
00:51:55,600 --> 00:51:58,999
It looks like that day was the
same date as the autumn festival.

678
00:52:00,007 --> 00:52:01,577
The point of impact was here.

679
00:52:02,620 --> 00:52:06,976
At 8:42 p.m. it fell right around where
people were gathered for the festival.

680
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:13,641
Over 500 died.

681
00:52:14,182 --> 00:52:16,192
It was a third of the town's population,

682
00:52:16,746 --> 00:52:18,995
and now nobody lives in Itomori anymore.

683
00:52:28,020 --> 00:52:29,317
Teshigawara...

684
00:52:29,860 --> 00:52:30,889
and Sayaka.

685
00:52:35,703 --> 00:52:37,272
Huh? That's her?

686
00:52:37,630 --> 00:52:39,544
You were wrong. You gotta be.

687
00:52:39,824 --> 00:52:42,887
After all, this girl here died three years ago!

688
00:52:43,681 --> 00:52:47,899
Just two or three weeks ago she said
that I'd be able to see the comet.

689
00:52:48,673 --> 00:52:49,593
That means...!

690
00:52:50,623 --> 00:52:52,188
You're dreaming right now.

691
00:52:52,914 --> 00:52:53,320
I...

692
00:52:53,367 --> 00:52:54,284
aren't you?

693
00:52:56,318 --> 00:52:57,094
I...

694
00:52:59,474 --> 00:53:01,206
What... was I?

695
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:16,421
Sounds lively over there.

696
00:53:16,820 --> 00:53:19,707
They only have one room left. I'm really sorry.

697
00:53:19,814 --> 00:53:20,866
It's not a problem.

698
00:53:22,180 --> 00:53:23,275
How's Taki?

699
00:53:23,508 --> 00:53:25,748
He's still reading articles on Itomori.

700
00:53:26,041 --> 00:53:29,848
He's going through all those newspapers
and magazines at random. Seems obsessive.

701
00:53:34,980 --> 00:53:36,029
What is it?

702
00:53:36,246 --> 00:53:38,216
Oh, sorry. You smoke, huh?

703
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:41,541
Yeah. I did quit at one point.

704
00:53:42,912 --> 00:53:45,256
What do you think about what Taki's been saying?

705
00:53:48,806 --> 00:53:50,676
I had feelings for him, you know.

706
00:53:51,547 --> 00:53:53,092
The way he's been recently.

707
00:53:53,671 --> 00:53:55,661
I mean, he was a nice guy before,

708
00:53:55,828 --> 00:53:57,442
but he's even nicer now.

709
00:53:58,278 --> 00:54:01,702
Kind of... frantic. It was cute.

710
00:54:02,703 --> 00:54:06,655
Although I do think what he's been
telling us is definitely strange sounding.

711
00:54:09,161 --> 00:54:11,971
But in the end,
the fact remains that Taki's met someone,

712
00:54:12,001 --> 00:54:14,194
and that someone is the reason he changed.

713
00:54:15,816 --> 00:54:17,319
That much is for sure.

714
00:54:32,977 --> 00:54:34,495
It was all just a dream.

715
00:54:36,463 --> 00:54:38,058
I recognized the landscape

716
00:54:38,330 --> 00:54:41,403
because I unconsciously remembered
the news from three years ago.

717
00:54:43,756 --> 00:54:46,713
If it's not that, is she... a ghost?

718
00:54:46,992 --> 00:54:47,849
Or...

719
00:54:48,852 --> 00:54:51,720
did I just make it up? The whole thing.

720
00:54:55,649 --> 00:54:57,302
What was her name?

721
00:54:58,116 --> 00:54:59,324
I can't remember.

722
00:55:01,933 --> 00:55:04,457
Tsukasa said he was gonna go ahead and take a bath.

723
00:55:04,734 --> 00:55:05,883
Miss Okudera.

724
00:55:06,385 --> 00:55:08,191
Uh... I, um...

725
00:55:08,924 --> 00:55:11,622
I realize I've been saying a lot of strange things.

726
00:55:12,492 --> 00:55:14,469
I'm really sorry, and thank you.

727
00:55:23,135 --> 00:55:25,475
Braided cords. Pretty.

728
00:55:26,500 --> 00:55:27,945
That band on your wrist,

729
00:55:28,432 --> 00:55:29,499
that's one, isn't it?

730
00:55:30,530 --> 00:55:32,693
Oh, this thing? Guess so.

731
00:55:33,070 --> 00:55:36,048
Somebody... Someone gave it to me.

732
00:55:36,849 --> 00:55:39,540
I wear it sometimes as kind of a lucky charm.

733
00:55:42,300 --> 00:55:43,605
Who was it?

734
00:55:46,080 --> 00:55:49,133
It's late. Why don't you go down and take a bath too?

735
00:55:49,300 --> 00:55:50,825
Sure. Wait.

736
00:55:54,152 --> 00:55:56,692
Yeah, someone who makes these.

737
00:55:57,034 --> 00:55:58,701
They once told me something.

738
00:55:59,001 --> 00:56:01,578
The cords represent the flow of time.

739
00:56:01,970 --> 00:56:05,086
They twist and tangle, unravel and connect.

740
00:56:05,580 --> 00:56:07,837
And how that's what time is.

741
00:56:10,086 --> 00:56:11,341
Maybe if I could...

742
00:56:37,844 --> 00:56:38,971
Taki.

743
00:56:39,480 --> 00:56:40,750
Taki.

744
00:56:41,400 --> 00:56:42,596
Taki!

745
00:56:44,553 --> 00:56:45,902
Don't you remember?

746
00:57:08,940 --> 00:57:10,019
Taki...

747
00:57:34,411 --> 00:57:36,369
Eat this bento up there.

748
00:57:37,516 --> 00:57:39,258
Your drawing of Itomori,

749
00:57:40,174 --> 00:57:41,451
you did a real good job.

750
00:58:19,212 --> 00:58:21,105
They assemble and take shape.

751
00:58:21,760 --> 00:58:23,167
They twist, tangle,

752
00:58:23,583 --> 00:58:26,979
unravel now and then, break and reconnect.

753
00:58:28,370 --> 00:58:29,918
That's what a union is.

754
00:58:30,749 --> 00:58:32,333
What time is.

755
00:58:43,722 --> 00:58:44,821
There it is!

756
00:58:47,281 --> 00:58:48,423
It's really there.

757
00:58:49,792 --> 00:58:51,893
It wasn't a dream.

758
00:59:23,153 --> 00:59:26,337
What lies ahead... is the netherworld.

759
00:59:49,136 --> 00:59:50,470
It's still here.

760
00:59:52,612 --> 00:59:54,435
This was Yotsuha's,

761
00:59:55,279 --> 00:59:56,546
and this was mine.

762
00:59:59,330 --> 01:00:00,809
This was before the comet.

763
01:00:01,540 --> 01:00:03,600
So when I switched places with her,

764
01:00:04,196 --> 01:00:06,176
it was also three years in the past.

765
01:00:08,091 --> 01:00:11,031
Our times got tangled somehow.

766
01:00:12,523 --> 01:00:14,683
This is half of her.

767
01:00:29,759 --> 01:00:30,559
Musubi.

768
01:00:32,080 --> 01:00:34,815
If it's true, and time can be unraveled,

769
01:00:35,876 --> 01:00:37,747
just give me one chance.

770
01:00:52,651 --> 01:00:53,777
A comet!

771
01:01:59,203 --> 01:02:01,852
Your name's going to be Mitsuha.

772
01:02:08,600 --> 01:02:11,105
Both of you are my treasures.

773
01:02:11,130 --> 01:02:13,321
You're going to be a big sister.

774
01:02:16,040 --> 01:02:18,396
I'm so sorry, me dears.

775
01:02:20,536 --> 01:02:23,604
Dad, when is Mommy coming home?

776
01:02:24,710 --> 01:02:26,027
I couldn't help her.

777
01:02:26,040 --> 01:02:28,060
Get a hold of yourself!

778
01:02:28,080 --> 01:02:29,644
Who cares about the shrine?!

779
01:02:29,660 --> 01:02:31,204
But you're in charge now!

780
01:02:31,220 --> 01:02:33,525
I loved Futaba! Not Miyamizu Shrine.

781
01:02:33,550 --> 01:02:34,805
Get out!

782
01:02:38,422 --> 01:02:41,587
Now listen to me, girls, starting today,

783
01:02:41,941 --> 01:02:44,016
you'll be living with Grandma.

784
01:02:48,580 --> 01:02:50,259
Who am I?

785
01:02:50,410 --> 01:02:51,434
Who are you?

786
01:02:51,720 --> 01:02:53,235
Don't be full of yourself!

787
01:02:53,250 --> 01:02:55,131
Like you have a girlfriend.

788
01:02:55,270 --> 01:02:56,369
Must be nice.

789
01:02:56,680 --> 01:02:58,934
They've probably met up about now.

790
01:03:00,280 --> 01:03:01,369
Why am I...?

791
01:03:01,500 --> 01:03:02,844
I'm going to Tokyo.

792
01:03:02,880 --> 01:03:04,864
What? Wait, Sis!

793
01:03:07,394 --> 01:03:08,147
Grandma.

794
01:03:08,962 --> 01:03:10,720
would you mind doing me a favor?

795
01:03:11,837 --> 01:03:13,483
Oh, yeah, the comet.

796
01:03:14,900 --> 01:03:17,283
It'll be at its brightest today, right?

797
01:03:18,010 --> 01:03:20,103
Mitsuha! Don't go there!

798
01:03:21,150 --> 01:03:25,200
Mitsuha, You've gotta get out of
town before the comet strikes!

799
01:03:27,954 --> 01:03:29,692
Mitsuha, run!

800
01:03:30,560 --> 01:03:33,353
Mitsuha. Mitsuha!

801
01:03:33,515 --> 01:03:36,163
Mitsuha!

802
01:03:53,764 --> 01:03:56,385
Mitsuha. She's alive.

803
01:04:07,509 --> 01:04:09,451
Let me guess, you're touching your boo...

804
01:04:12,326 --> 01:04:13,754
Her sister!

805
01:04:16,100 --> 01:04:18,541
Yotsuha!

806
01:04:21,552 --> 01:04:23,867
I think she's finally lost it.

807
01:04:24,020 --> 01:04:27,179
