1030
01:19:35,136 --> 01:19:36,086
Sorry.

1031
01:19:36,540 --> 01:19:38,637
Wait, is that...?

1032
01:19:39,357 --> 01:19:42,981
Oh, yeah, it's yours, but you visited before I knew you.

1033
01:19:43,596 --> 01:19:45,131
So I didn't know who you were.

1034
01:19:46,195 --> 01:19:46,968
Here.

1035
01:19:47,799 --> 01:19:49,578
I kept it for three years.

1036
01:19:50,180 --> 01:19:51,950
But I think it's time you got it back.

1037
01:20:02,636 --> 01:20:03,596
What do ya think?

1038
01:20:03,800 --> 01:20:06,582
Oh, uh, well... It's not bad.

1039
01:20:06,821 --> 01:20:08,335
Oh, you're lying!

1040
01:20:09,635 --> 01:20:10,604
Busted.

1041
01:20:10,698 --> 01:20:12,544
Why you gotta be like that?

1042
01:20:27,264 --> 01:20:31,657
Hey, Mitsuha, you still have a lot to do. Listen.

1043
01:20:32,630 --> 01:20:33,640
It's coming.

1044
01:20:34,169 --> 01:20:36,664
Don't worry. You still have enough time.

1045
01:20:36,855 --> 01:20:38,764
I'll do my best.

1046
01:20:40,406 --> 01:20:42,982
It looks like magic hour's almost...

1047
01:20:43,309 --> 01:20:44,091
...over.

1048
01:20:46,590 --> 01:20:47,679
Hey, Mitsuha.

1049
01:20:48,125 --> 01:20:50,449
Just so we don't forget things when we wake up.

1050
01:20:55,149 --> 01:20:56,758
Let's write down our names.

1051
01:20:57,710 --> 01:20:58,512
Here.

1052
01:21:10,780 --> 01:21:11,790
Mitsuha?

1053
01:21:14,456 --> 01:21:16,802
Hey, Mitsuha?

1054
01:21:25,334 --> 01:21:27,110
I was planning to tell you...

1055
01:21:28,670 --> 01:21:30,571
...that wherever you are in the world,

1056
01:21:30,744 --> 01:21:33,641
I swear that I'll find you again, no matter what.

1057
01:21:37,150 --> 01:21:39,499
Your name... is Mitsuha.

1058
01:21:40,920 --> 01:21:43,184
It'll be okay. I'll remember.

1059
01:21:43,660 --> 01:21:47,697
Mitsuha, Mitsuha, Mitsuha! Your name's Mitsuha!

1060
01:21:48,010 --> 01:21:49,179
Your name is...

1061
01:22:00,350 --> 01:22:01,039
Who

1062
01:22:01,860 --> 01:22:03,008
are you?

1063
01:22:04,966 --> 01:22:07,896
And what did I even come here for?

1064
01:22:08,801 --> 01:22:11,705
I came... I came all this way to see her!

1065
01:22:12,076 --> 01:22:13,673
I came to save her.

1066
01:22:13,863 --> 01:22:15,576
I wanted her to be alive.

1067
01:22:15,986 --> 01:22:17,368
Who was it again?

1068
01:22:17,530 --> 01:22:18,307
Who?

1069
01:22:18,530 --> 01:22:20,094
Who did I come to see?

1070
01:22:20,498 --> 01:22:21,855
Someone precious.

1071
01:22:21,964 --> 01:22:24,011
Someone that I don't wanna forget.

1072
01:22:24,080 --> 01:22:25,850
Someone I shouldn't!

1073
01:22:26,670 --> 01:22:27,531
Who was it?

1074
01:22:27,920 --> 01:22:29,142
Who was it?

1075
01:22:29,579 --> 01:22:31,577
Who? Who?

1076
01:22:31,801 --> 01:22:33,283
What's your name?!

1077
01:22:48,360 --> 01:22:51,664
Taki. Taki. Taki!

1078
01:22:52,164 --> 01:22:55,787
It'll be fine. I'll remember. I'll never forget!

1079
01:22:56,281 --> 01:22:58,367
Taki. Taki!

1080
01:22:58,767 --> 01:23:01,553
Your name is Taki!

1081
01:23:16,193 --> 01:23:17,391
Teshi!

1082
01:23:17,700 --> 01:23:18,462
Mitsuha!

1083
01:23:19,187 --> 01:23:20,684
Where the heck have you been?

1084
01:23:20,709 --> 01:23:22,529
He said sorry for breaking your bike.

1085
01:23:22,655 --> 01:23:24,403
Wha...? Who did?

1086
01:23:24,420 --> 01:23:25,190
I did!

1087
01:23:26,520 --> 01:23:28,599
You're gonna have to explain it to me later.

1088
01:23:33,290 --> 01:23:35,907
That thing is going to fall, right? For real?

1089
01:23:36,167 --> 01:23:38,392
For real. I saw it with my own eyes!

1090
01:23:38,526 --> 01:23:40,439
What? You did, huh?

1091
01:23:40,969 --> 01:23:43,025
Well, I guess it's settled then.

1092
01:23:44,287 --> 01:23:46,175
We're both officially criminals.

1093
01:23:47,876 --> 01:23:51,189
What? Do I really have to?

1094
01:23:51,222 --> 01:23:52,919
Once the town's power goes out,

1095
01:23:52,944 --> 01:23:55,130
the emergency generators will kick on right away.

1096
01:23:55,237 --> 01:23:57,341
Use the broadcast equipment once it does.

1097
01:23:57,506 --> 01:23:58,674
Don't be scared, Saya.

1098
01:23:58,853 --> 01:24:01,002
And repeat it as many times as you can.

1099
01:24:02,050 --> 01:24:03,495
You can do it!

1100
01:24:03,760 --> 01:24:06,749
Aw, nuts. It's do or die!

1101
01:24:13,040 --> 01:24:14,485
Shouldn't it be going off?

1102
01:24:14,500 --> 01:24:15,674
Hell if I know!

1103
01:24:26,920 --> 01:24:27,692
What was that?

1104
01:24:27,717 --> 01:24:29,648
That was pretty loud too. Look over there!

1105
01:24:55,210 --> 01:24:56,784
Hey, look! Up there!

1106
01:25:06,580 --> 01:25:09,421
This is Itomori Town Hall.

1107
01:25:09,840 --> 01:25:11,872
Reports of an explosion at the substation are coming in.

1108
01:25:11,897 --> 01:25:12,832
Explosion?

1109
01:25:13,500 --> 01:25:15,035
Did I just hear that right?

1110
01:25:15,060 --> 01:25:18,802
Wildfires are possible,
as well as the threat of more explosions.

1111
01:25:19,424 --> 01:25:21,617
Residents in he following areas,

1112
01:25:21,812 --> 01:25:25,372
please evacuate to Itomori High School immediately.

1113
01:25:26,170 --> 01:25:27,932
Kadoiri District

1114
01:25:28,537 --> 01:25:30,033
Sakagami District...

1115
01:25:30,160 --> 01:25:31,160
Honey, we should go.

1116
01:25:31,170 --> 01:25:32,962
The broadcast isn't coming from us?

1117
01:25:33,054 --> 01:25:34,336
Well, who the hell is it then?

1118
01:25:34,370 --> 01:25:36,330
Miyamori District.

1119
01:25:37,189 --> 01:25:39,032
Oyazawa District.

1120
01:25:39,850 --> 01:25:41,335
Let's go, Mitsuha!

1121
01:25:43,393 --> 01:25:44,442
Teshi!

1122
01:25:50,970 --> 01:25:54,445
Everyone, run! There's a wildfire!

1123
01:25:54,525 --> 01:25:56,575
Wildfire! Please run!

1124
01:25:56,600 --> 01:25:58,464
Get outta here! Run!

1125
01:25:58,489 --> 01:26:00,848
It's not safe here! Please evacuate!

1126
01:26:01,512 --> 01:26:04,944
It's not working. We're running outta time! Mitsuha!

1127
01:26:06,433 --> 01:26:07,275
What's wrong?

1128
01:26:08,340 --> 01:26:09,608
What is it?

1129
01:26:10,370 --> 01:26:12,942
I can't remember what his name is anymore!

1130
01:26:15,010 --> 01:26:16,508
What is with you?!

1131
01:26:16,681 --> 01:26:18,636
You're the one who started all of this!

1132
01:26:19,229 --> 01:26:21,862
We can't evacuate everyone without firefighters!

1133
01:26:22,516 --> 01:26:24,816
Get going! You gotta convince your old man!

1134
01:26:27,225 --> 01:26:29,038
This is Itomori Town Hall.

1135
01:26:30,840 --> 01:26:33,066
Reports of an explosion at the substation are coming in.

1136
01:26:33,090 --> 01:26:36,231
Everybody! Get to the high school! Hurry!

1137
01:26:38,950 --> 01:26:40,593
Oh, it's Mitsuha.

1138
01:26:43,670 --> 01:26:45,843
Why would terrorists attack way out here?

1139
01:26:45,868 --> 01:26:46,909
What is Chubu Electric saying?

1140
01:26:46,934 --> 01:26:48,248
They're still checking.

1141
01:26:48,530 --> 01:26:50,827
Any update? No wildfires yet?

1142
01:26:51,099 --> 01:26:52,581
You're sure? Got it.

1143
01:26:54,421 --> 01:26:56,630
Make them stop this broadcast immediately!

1144
01:26:56,687 --> 01:26:58,462
Haven't you located its source yet?!

1145
01:26:58,490 --> 01:27:01,242
Mayor! The Takayama sensor station just called!

1146
01:27:02,070 --> 01:27:03,674
From the high school?

1147
01:27:04,050 --> 01:27:07,258
Once again, residents in the following areas,

1148
01:27:07,377 --> 01:27:10,145
please evacuate to Itomori High... Ah!

1149
01:27:10,170 --> 01:27:12,269
What're you doing? Turn that off!

1150
01:27:15,015 --> 01:27:16,068
They got Saya!

1151
01:27:16,299 --> 01:27:17,107
Oh, no!

1152
01:27:20,810 --> 01:27:23,434
What were you doing, Natori? I swear.

1153
01:27:27,141 --> 01:27:29,556
This is Itomori Town Hall.

1154
01:27:30,652 --> 01:27:34,107
We are currently confirming the reports of the accident.

1155
01:27:35,196 --> 01:27:40,116
We instruct all residents to remain calm
and stay where they are till further notice.

1156
01:27:40,140 --> 01:27:41,557
I guess we have to stay put.

1157
01:27:42,010 --> 01:27:42,901
What is going on?

1158
01:27:42,910 --> 01:27:44,385
So stay on standby.

1159
01:27:45,199 --> 01:27:47,971
Come on, they said everyone should evacuate!

1160
01:27:48,210 --> 01:27:50,398
The high school's the evacuation center!

1161
01:27:50,420 --> 01:27:51,410
Katsuhiko!

1162
01:27:54,697 --> 01:27:57,283
Tell me. What do you think you're doing?

1163
01:28:00,551 --> 01:28:01,846
Sorry, Mitsuha.

1164
01:28:03,310 --> 01:28:04,566
This is the end.

1165
01:28:07,220 --> 01:28:10,257
Oh my god. It's actually splitting apart.

1166
01:28:17,520 --> 01:28:20,556
Look at that! The comet has split into two large parts,

1167
01:28:20,581 --> 01:28:23,314
and meteors are now falling to earth!

1168
01:28:23,910 --> 01:28:26,068
I don't believe anyone could've predicted this.

1169
01:28:26,090 --> 01:28:28,278
Either way, we have quite the mystical view here.

1170
01:28:28,300 --> 01:28:31,576
So what does the comet's nucleus splitting mean for us?

1171
01:28:31,880 --> 01:28:33,444
The comet's not within the Roche limit,

1172
01:28:33,480 --> 01:28:37,263
so the nucleus itself must've had a
structural weakness for this to happen.

1173
01:28:37,520 --> 01:28:42,539
Comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 broke apart
and collided with Jupiter in 1994.

1174
01:28:42,956 --> 01:28:43,676
There were at least 21 fragments then.

1175
01:28:43,700 --> 01:28:45,086
I'm going outside to take a look.

1176
01:28:45,110 --> 01:28:46,486
The fragments will likely burn up

1177
01:28:46,500 --> 01:28:49,896
well before reaching the ground,
The probability of a meteor actually landing...

1178
01:28:49,930 --> 01:28:54,444
Scientists were already intently examining the
comet, but never foresaw this development.

1179
01:28:54,490 --> 01:28:56,114
To predict the trajectory...

1180
01:28:56,130 --> 01:28:58,123
As we stand here witnessing this spectacle,

1181
01:28:58,558 --> 01:29:01,382
unassisted and with our bare eyes,

1182
01:29:01,500 --> 01:29:05,668
it strikes me that living in such an age
has never felt more fortunate than now.

1183
01:29:09,541 --> 01:29:13,272
Hey. Who are you?

1184
01:29:16,690 --> 01:29:19,195
Who? Who?

1185
01:29:20,104 --> 01:29:21,367
Who is he?

1186
01:29:21,600 --> 01:29:23,567
Someone precious.

1187
01:29:23,880 --> 01:29:25,371
Someone I shouldn't forget.

1188
01:29:25,944 --> 01:29:27,768
Someone I didn't want to!

1189
01:29:28,596 --> 01:29:32,737
Who? Who? Who are you?

1190
01:29:33,210 --> 01:29:34,757
What's your name?

1191
01:29:40,760 --> 01:29:41,755
Oh, no.

1192
01:30:01,556 --> 01:30:03,821
So that we don't forget things when we wake up,

1193
01:30:04,280 --> 01:30:05,785
let's write down our names.

1194
01:30:14,683 --> 01:30:18,576
"I LOVE YOU"

1195
01:30:33,560 --> 01:30:38,482
Writing this... doesn't help. I won't know your name.

1196
01:30:51,860 --> 01:30:52,999
Dad!

1197
01:30:54,640 --> 01:30:55,333
Mitsuha?

1198
01:30:55,416 --> 01:30:56,558
There you are!

1199
01:30:56,720 --> 01:30:58,344
Don't tell me you're back.

1200
01:31:02,600 --> 01:31:05,474
It was almost like seeing something out of a dream.

1201
01:31:06,470 --> 01:31:09,928
Nothing more or less than a breathtaking view.

1202
01:32:44,186 --> 01:32:45,599
Why am I here?

1203
01:32:47,063 --> 01:32:48,409
What am I doing?

1204
01:32:57,970 --> 01:33:01,257
Next is Yoyogi. Yoyogi.

1205
01:33:14,238 --> 01:33:17,540
The doors are closing. Please be careful.

1206
01:33:20,487 --> 01:33:22,654
I'm always searching for something.

1207
01:33:23,326 --> 01:33:28,021
This feeling has consumed me for some time.

1208
01:33:30,213 --> 01:33:32,173
The reason I applied for this position...

1209
01:33:32,276 --> 01:33:35,572
The landscapes people live in...
To build a city's landscape...

1210
01:33:35,727 --> 01:33:38,478
Even Tokyo, it might vanish too one day.

1211
01:33:38,699 --> 01:33:41,362
And so, I wanna make landscapes that

1212
01:33:41,603 --> 01:33:42,885
How should I put this?

1213
01:33:43,073 --> 01:33:46,524
That can continue to warm people's hearts.

1214
01:33:48,140 --> 01:33:50,427
That bad? How many does that make it?

1215
01:33:50,530 --> 01:33:51,866
I've stopped counting.

1216
01:33:51,880 --> 01:33:53,365
Doesn't sound too promising.

1217
01:33:53,380 --> 01:33:54,152
Who asked you?

1218
01:33:54,160 --> 01:33:55,942
That suit could be the problem.

1219
01:33:55,960 --> 01:33:57,584
It looks just like yours!

1220
01:33:57,660 --> 01:33:59,036
Well, I have two offers.

1221
01:33:59,060 --> 01:34:00,486
I have eight myself.

1222
01:34:06,119 --> 01:34:10,709
Is what I'm searching for... someone? Or somewhere?

1223
01:34:11,919 --> 01:34:14,590
Or am I just searching for the right job?

1224
01:34:15,243 --> 01:34:16,648
I don't even really know.

1225
01:34:17,924 --> 01:34:20,504
Oh, You're job hunting, huh?

1226
01:34:20,550 --> 01:34:22,291
I haven't had much luck though.

1227
01:34:23,014 --> 01:34:25,182
Hey, maybe it's the suit that's killing your chances.

1228
01:34:25,255 --> 01:34:27,081
Does it really look that bad on me?

1229
01:34:32,171 --> 01:34:34,211
So why the sudden call today?

1230
01:34:34,724 --> 01:34:39,260
I was in the area for work and I figured
it had been a while since I saw your face.

1231
01:34:42,068 --> 01:34:45,614
Remember that one time when we
went all the way to Itomori?

1232
01:34:45,950 --> 01:34:49,037
You were still in high school back then, so it was...

1233
01:34:49,890 --> 01:34:50,939
Five years ago.

1234
01:34:51,044 --> 01:34:52,137
That long?

1235
01:34:53,058 --> 01:34:55,893
It seems like... I've forgotten a lot.

1236
01:34:57,252 --> 01:34:59,297
I don't remember all that much either,

1237
01:34:59,779 --> 01:35:00,819
about back then.

1238
01:35:01,780 --> 01:35:03,322
Maybe we argued.

1239
01:35:03,940 --> 01:35:06,712
She and Tsukasa went back to Tokyo without me.

1240
01:35:07,939 --> 01:35:10,331
I spent the night alone on some mountain.

1241
01:35:11,500 --> 01:35:12,965
That's about all I remember.

1242
01:35:16,317 --> 01:35:18,264
But at one point in time,

1243
01:35:18,606 --> 01:35:22,503
I found myself strangely drawn to
the incident involving that comet.

1244
01:35:25,427 --> 01:35:28,616
A fragment of the comet destroyed
a town in that disaster.

1245
01:35:29,385 --> 01:35:33,262
But miraculously, most of the people
living in the town were unhurt.

1246
01:35:34,629 --> 01:35:37,337
The town happened to be holding
an emergency drill that day,

1247
01:35:37,940 --> 01:35:40,633
and most of its residents were outside the impact zone.

1248
01:35:42,488 --> 01:35:46,840
The sheer luck and coincidence of it
all sparked various conspiracy theories.

1249
01:35:48,217 --> 01:35:50,194
I read a lot of articles about it back then.

1250
01:35:51,114 --> 01:35:52,247
I was kind of obsessed.

1251
01:35:53,542 --> 01:35:56,240
But whatever the reason I had for my interest,

1252
01:35:56,444 --> 01:35:58,057
is a mystery to me now.

1253
01:36:00,213 --> 01:36:02,183
I didn't even know anybody in that town.

1254
01:36:06,166 --> 01:36:08,633
Thanks for today. This is far enough.

1255
01:36:10,103 --> 01:36:15,519
I do hope that at some point, you'll find happiness too.

1256
01:36:19,439 --> 01:36:21,775
I feel like I'm always searching.

1257
01:36:22,504 --> 01:36:25,331
For something. Someone.

1258
01:36:36,936 --> 01:36:39,948
I feel like I do wanna go to one more bridal fair.

1259
01:36:40,047 --> 01:36:41,335
They're all the same.

1260
01:36:41,470 --> 01:36:43,805
A Shinto wedding sure sounds nice too.

1261
01:36:43,830 --> 01:36:46,100
You said you wanted to be married in a chapel!

1262
01:36:46,533 --> 01:36:48,042
Oh! That reminds me, Teshi.

1263
01:36:48,297 --> 01:36:50,992
Would ya please shave before the ceremony?

1264
01:36:51,112 --> 01:36:52,900
I'm going on a diet for it, ya know?

1265
01:36:53,230 --> 01:36:55,250
She says as she's eating a cake.

1266
01:36:55,430 --> 01:36:57,068
I'll get serious tomorrow.

1267
01:37:56,280 --> 01:37:58,847
The landscape of a town that's no longer there.

1268
01:37:59,569 --> 01:38:02,816
Why does looking at it make my heart feel so tight?

1269
01:39:23,797 --> 01:39:25,236
I was always searching.

1270
01:39:25,637 --> 01:39:26,643
Searching for...

1271
01:39:28,078 --> 01:39:29,231
...someone!

1272
01:40:26,923 --> 01:40:28,101
Excuse me!

1273
01:40:28,539 --> 01:40:29,459
Haven't we...?

1274
01:40:30,026 --> 01:40:32,473
Have I met you somewhere?

1275
01:40:41,400 --> 01:40:42,747
I thought so too!

1276
01:40:47,599 --> 01:40:50,132
Can I ask you... your name?

